File: Roxette's Marie Fredriksson performs during the rehearsal of the Popkomm Music Fair Gala in Cologne August 15, 2001. JOHANNESBURG - Roxette singer, Marie Fredriksson, has died aged 61. The Swedish singer reportedly passed away on Monday after battling cancer for 17 years. Known for the songs, Joy Ride, It must have been love and Listen to your heart, the pop band rose to fame in the 80's and 90's. Her band mate, Per Gessle paid tribute to Fredricksson saying, "I am honoured to have met your talent + generosity... Things will never be the same". 